$ Business Process Execution Language
-
@ BPEL

aka: WS-BPEL (WS stands for web service)

BPEL is an → development/XML[XML]-based (meta-like) language to specify business processes with the intention to *act as the central controller of the business process*.

BPEL provides a standard way in a → development/Software-design/SOA[SOA] world.

BPEL is not a → development/languages[programming language].

BPEL is an orchestration language rather than a choreography language.

BPELscript is a language to specify BPEL processes.

sa:
  → development/web/service[web services]
